.TH phasordecomp 1 "March 2026" "Phasor 3.1.0" "Phasor Manual"
.SH NAME
phasordecomp \- Phasor bytecode disassembler
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B phasordecomp
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.I input.phsb
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B phasordecomp
reads a compiled Phasor bytecode file (.phsb) and converts it into a human-readable Phasor intermediate representation file (.phir). The resulting IR file can be inspected, modified, and re-assembled back into bytecode using
.BR phasorassembler (1).
.PP
This tool is useful for debugging compiled programs, auditing generated bytecode, and understanding the low-level output of the Phasor compiler toolchain.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-o ", " \-\-output " " \fIFILE\fR
Specify the output file path. If not provided, the output file is placed alongside the input file with the same base name and a
.I .phir
extension.
.TP
.BR \-n ", " \-\-nologo
Suppress the banner and copyright information.
.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-silent
Suppress all output except errors. Implies
.BR \-\-nologo .
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Display help information and exit.
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
.I input.phsb
The compiled Phasor bytecode file to disassemble. Only one input file may be specified.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I *.phsb
Phasor compiled bytecode files \fBPHSB(5)\fR
.TP
.I *.phir
Phasor intermediate representation output files \fBPHIR(5)\fR
.SH EXAMPLES
Disassemble a bytecode file (output written to program.phir):
.PP
.nf
.RS
phasordecomp program.phsb
.RE
.fi
.PP
Disassemble with an explicit output path:
.PP
.nf
.RS
phasordecomp program.phsb -o inspect/program.phir
.RE
.fi
.PP
Disassemble silently (no stdout, errors only):
.PP
.nf
.RS
phasordecomp -s program.phsb -o program.phir
.RE
.fi
.PP
Disassemble, edit the IR, then re-assemble:
.PP
.nf
.RS
phasordecomp program.phsb
$EDITOR program.phir
phasorassembler program.phir
.RE
.fi
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Successful disassembly
.TP
.B 1
Disassembly failed due to an invalid or unreadable bytecode file, a write error, or invalid arguments
.SH DIAGNOSTICS
On success,
.B phasordecomp
prints the output file path to standard output unless
.BR \-\-silent
is specified. Errors are always written to standard error.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR PHSB (5),
.BR PHIR (5),
.BR phasorassembler (1),
.BR phasorcompiler (1),
.BR phasorvm (1),
.BR phasor (1)
